summary:
Motivated graduate with a MSc degree in mechanical engineering with a broad range of skills looking for a career opportunity in a dynamic work environment. 

Offering my problem solving attitude and innovative thinking to advance development of current and future products.

I did two professional internships where I worked in a team environment and thus gained irreplaceable experience and valuable communication skills. I am a responsible and reliable person with the ability to reason and make difficult decisions when needed.

My first internship was at Elcon Geraetebau d.o.o. included turning and milling related jobs. For my second professional practice I worked at Havyard Design & Engineering Rijeka where I was learning and acquiring new skills while visiting different departments in naval design and development company. During my study I worked on multiple student jobs. On my last student job at Vulpes i was a part of the development and assembly of air purification devices.
